</Example>

### Keep Mounted

Use `forceMount` on `CollapsibleDefaultPanel` or `CollapsiblePanel` to preserve internal state — such as form inputs — when the panel is collapsed.

<Example demo="collapsible-force-mount-demo">
  <CollapsibleForceMountDemo />
</Example>

### Accordion Pattern

Control which item is open to create an accordion where only one item can be expanded at a time.

<Example demo="collapsible-accordion-demo">
  <CollapsibleAccordionDemo />
</Example>

## Sub-components

| Component | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `Collapsible` | Manages open state. Use `bind:open` or pass `open` and `onOpenChange` for controlled mode. |
| `CollapsibleRoot` | Alias for `Collapsible`. |
| `CollapsibleTrigger` | Button that toggles visibility. Add classes for custom styling. |
| `CollapsiblePanel` | Container for collapsible content. |
| `CollapsibleContent` | Alias for `CollapsiblePanel`. |
| `CollapsibleDefaultTrigger` | Pre-styled trigger with text label and animated caret icon. |
| `CollapsibleDefaultPanel` | Pre-styled panel with border-left accent and standard spacing. |

## API Reference

### Collapsible / CollapsibleRoot

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `open` | `boolean` | `false` | Whether the panel is visible. Bind with `bind:open` for two-way state. |
| `onOpenChange` | `(open: boolean) => void` | — | Callback when open state changes. |
| `onOpenChangeComplete` | `(open: boolean) => void` | — | Callback after the open change completes. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Whether the collapsible is disabled. |
| `id` | `string` | — | Root element ID. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional CSS classes. |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Trigger and panel content. |

### CollapsibleTrigger

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Trigger label or content. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Whether the trigger is disabled. |
| `id` | `string` | — | Trigger element ID. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional CSS classes. |

### CollapsiblePanel / CollapsibleContent

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Panel content. |
| `forceMount` | `boolean` | — | Keep the panel mounted in the DOM when closed. |
| `hiddenUntilFound` | `boolean` | — | Use browser find-in-page support for hidden content. |
| `id` | `string` | — | Panel element ID. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional CSS classes. |

### CollapsibleDefaultTrigger

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Label displayed in the trigger. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Whether the trigger is disabled. |
| `id` | `string` | — | Trigger element ID. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional CSS classes. |

### CollapsibleDefaultPanel

Accepts the same props as `CollapsiblePanel`, with the default Kumo border-left accent and spacing applied.
